Police have routinely been conducting raids to enforce lockdown regulations but several rallies have been held recently in contravention of safety protocols. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police are on the defensive. They insist they aren't turning a blind eye to large gatherings like protests. READ: Thousands march to demand COVID jabs in South Africa This week, a big crowd of EFF members gathered outside the office of the health regulator, SAHPRA, in contravention of lockdown regulations. Many weren't social distancing or wearing masks but police say they must first conduct an investigation before any action can be taken against the organisers.